<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 15 at 5:27PM CDT  by NWS Birmingham</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern
Talladega County through 600 PM CDT...
At 527 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Alpine, or 8 miles northeast of Childersburg, moving south at 5 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Sylacauga, Childersburg, Vincent, Oak Grove, Bon Air, Sycamore,
Winterboro, Alpine, Logan Martin Dam and Mignon.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
